# ============================================================
# TIMELINE DETAIL OPERATIONS
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: operations
domain: detail
subdomain: timeline-detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines operational handling for timeline detail.

scope:
Covers milestone review, progression correction,
cancellation handling, replay inspection,
and containment of unsafe timeline exposure.

required_behavior:
- Support milestone review.
- Support cancellation and replay inspection.
- Support historical progression maintenance.
- Support milestone correction with preserved trace.
- Support containment for unsafe replay disclosure.

state_model:
timeline_detail_operational_state:
- prepared
- reviewed
- active
- cancelled
- completed
- archived
- replay_only
- contained

validation_rules:
- target_ref is required.
- milestone ordering must remain coherent.
- completed and cancelled stages must preserve history trace.
- replay-only detail must not appear in current-active mode.

transition_rules:
- prepared -> reviewed
- reviewed -> active
- active -> completed
- active -> cancelled
- completed -> replay_only
- cancelled -> replay_only
- replay_only -> archived
- active -> contained
- contained -> reviewed

operational_focus:
- progression review
- milestone correction handling
- replay-safe archival control
- cancellation-state review

failure_codes:
- TIMELINE_DETAIL_OP_REF_MISSING
- TIMELINE_DETAIL_OP_ORDER_INVALID
- TIMELINE_DETAIL_OP_MODE_CONFLICT
- TIMELINE_DETAIL_OP_HISTORY_TRACE_MISSING
